<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>John Pennekamp Coral Reef SP</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[First underwater state park in the US (1963). Glass-bottom boat tours and snorkel trips to the only living coral reef in the continental US.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-80.447300,25.086500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Robbie's Marina (Islamorada)</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Hand-feed enormous tarpon (nearly 2 m) at the dock — pelicans crash the line. Iconic Keys experience for $5.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-80.628000,24.924200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Pigeon Key</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Walkable historic island — original construction camp for Flagler's railroad. Small museum; reach by tram or walk on the old bridge.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-81.153800,24.701900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bahia Honda State Park</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Arguably the best beach in the Keys: turquoise water, good shade, snorkeling from shore. Old railroad bridge segment is photogenic.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-81.288000,24.658000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>National Key Deer Refuge</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Endemic miniature deer (about the size of a Labrador) — descended from white-tails marooned by sea-level rise after the last Ice Age. Approach No Name Key at dawn.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-81.385000,24.670000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Southernmost Point buoy</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Touristy painted concrete buoy in Key West. 90 mi (145 km) to Cuba. Photo-line reliably long.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-81.795000,24.546000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
